</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[264,1323,284,1902]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Etymology. Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Perez-Gelabert" authorityYear="2006" box="[528,638,1639,1664]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Eumecosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulum">
<emphasis box="[528,638,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">caerulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for blue, referring to the bright blue color of the scutum and scutellum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="42.[264,1323,284,1902]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Perez-Gelabert" authorityYear="2006" box="[432,707,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Eumecosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulum">
<emphasis box="[432,707,1718,1743]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Eumecosoma caerulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a member of the 
<emphasis box="[926,1061,1718,1743]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">pleuriticum</emphasis>
species group (
<bibRefCitation author="Fisher, E. M. &amp; Hespenheide, H." pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="610 - 613" refId="ref41860" refString="Fisher, E. M. &amp; Hespenheide, H. (1992) Taxonomy and biology of Central American robber flies with an illustrated key to the genera (Diptera: Asilidae). In Quintero Arias, D. and Aiello, A. (editors). Insects of Panama and Meso-America. Oxford University Press, Oxford, New York, Tokyo. 610 - 613 pp." type="book chapter" year="1992">Fisher and Hespenheide 1992</bibRefCitation>
), is the first species of this genus reported in the West Indies. It runs to 
<taxonomicName authority="Schiner (1868)" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[373,769,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Eumecosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallescens">
<emphasis box="[373,567,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">E. metallescens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schiner, J. R." box="[584,769,1796,1822]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="1 - 388" refId="ref43021" refString="Schiner, J. R. (1868) Diptera, pp. 1 - 388, 4 pls., in Reise der osterreichischen Fregatte Novara um die Erde, Zoologie 2 (1, B). Wien." type="book chapter" year="1868">Schiner (1868)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[863,917,1796,1822]" name="Peru" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Peru</collectingCountry>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Curran, C. H." box="[975,1169,1796,1822]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" refId="ref41263" refString="Curran, C. H. (1930) New American Asilidae (Diptera). American Museum Novitates, 425,1 - 21, 3 figs." type="book" year="1930">Curran's (1930)</bibRefCitation>
key but is distinguished from congeners by the color of the facial tomentum in the female and male antenna (
